message: Always start by cooking all raw proteins with the stove. Next, use water to wash all other ingredients (vegetables and grains). Once washed, cook these items with the stove. message: Focus on preparing items before combining. First, cook all raw proteins (egg, fish, bacon, beef, beans) with the stove. For vegetables (pepper, mushroom, carrot, tomato), use water to 'wash' them, then cook them with the stove. Once you have a selection of cooked proteins and cooked vegetables, combine them. The key to high value is to combine exactly three prepared items (e.g., two cooked proteins and one cooked vegetable, or one cooked protein and two cooked vegetables). Do not combine more than three items, as this often resets the value to zero. Grains (wheat, rice, tortilla, bread) didn't seem to contribute positively when added to a three-item dish.

message: Hello future player! My strategy, based on the previous hint, was to first cook all proteins with the stove. Next, wash all other ingredients (vegetables and grains) with water. Then, cook all of these washed ingredients using the stove. For combining, always start by combining a cooked protein with a cooked grain. This will give you a good base value. After that, add one cooked vegetable to make a three-item dish. Crucially, *never combine more than three items*, as this consistently reset the value to 0. Following these steps, I consistently achieved a score of 80.
